content.description: Start on good right hold, left crimp, and foot under roof. Traverse left to arete, then up. May or may not involve cutting feet depending on your technique/beta.
content.location: Head up trail behind pump house. Not as high up hill as Number Lover.

content.description: Start as Number Lover, but do not move left around boulder. Go straight up for mantle finish.
content.location: Hike up hill between pump house buildings. Boulder is left of and before the visible roof boulder higher up the hill.

content.description: Slabby warm up. Crux is getting established. Right foot dimple, right hand side pull, how will you get started? From there, friction is your friend for a couple moves and then, holds abound.
content.location: Follow trail between buildings. Boulder is left of Tenth Wife.

content.description: Sit start with good right hand pocket.  Moves up and left.  Finished using crack system on left side of arete.  Probably a direct finish for a harder grade - top out was still damp after cleaning, so didn't attempt.
content.location: Hike up hill between pump house buildings.  Boulder is left of and before the visible roof boulder higher up the hill.

content.description: There are a few boulders located up the hill behind the pump house.
